      "cell_type": "markdown",

        "id": "f4d5jEof3yqh"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Data Argumentation\n",
        "A common problem, is the amount of data available to enter the models, for models to present the expected results it is necessary for training to occur with a large amount of data (dataset), but in many cases the data needed to perform these tasks is not available.\n",
        "This is where the **Data Augmentation** technique comes in that, as the name suggests, allows us to augment our dataset in two ways:\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "*   Introducing disturbances in the original data. For example: taking an original image centered, we replicate it off-center, reversing axes…\n",
        "*   Using different distributions. Example: if we want to train a model to classify high-resolution images, we add low-resolution images, with noise… always maintaining the highest high-resolution ratio.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "OaQHT64I5wpc"
      },
      "source": [
        "At first, neural networks are not intelligent. For example, a poorly trained neural network would think that these three tennis balls shown below are distinct and unique images."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "l37sOvPH61IZ"
      },
      "source": [
        "![tenis ball.jpeg](data:image/jpeg;base64,)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "The same ball with some translations.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "eapL7NPU7GuS"
      },
      "source": [
        "So if we work with images, it is only necessary to make some small alterations to our dataset and we can achieve our goal.\n",
        "There are many ways to augment data with images, such as:\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "1.   Turn around (Flip)\n",
        "2.   Rotation\n",
        "\n",
        "1.   Scale\n",
        "2.   Cutout\n",
        "\n",
        "1.   Traslation\n",
        "2.   Gaussian noise\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Z4K618-0PK3m"
      },
      "source": [
        "The Keras library provides the ability to use data augmentation automatically when training a model.\n",
        "This is accomplished by using the ImageDataGenerator class.\n",
        "A variety of techniques are supported, as well as pixel scaling methods, such as:\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "*   The changes in the image (translations) through the arguments **width_shift_range** y **height_shift_range**.\n",
        "*  Turning the image around using the arguments **horizontal_flip** y **vertical_flip**.\n",
        "*   Image rotations through storyline **rotation_range**\n",
        "*   Image brightness using the argument **brightness_range**.\n",
        "*   Image zoom using the argument **zoom_range**.\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's independently look at examples of images after they have been magnified. It is common to use a variety of augmentation techniques at the same time during training.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "VauLlu8VtT4D"
      },
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt    #Library that allows graphing, very MATLAB style\n",
        "import numpy as np                  #Library that allows working with arrangement  \n",
        "from numpy import expand_dims       #Expand the array shape \n",
        "from keras.preprocessing.image import load_img    #From the Keras library for data augmentation, we load the image in the python image library (PIL) format\n",
        "from keras.preprocessing.image import img_to_array #will take a picture (PIL) and convert it to a matrix. If part of a PNG image, the values within the image will be between 0 and 255.\n",
        "from keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator #will take a picture (PIL) and convert it to a matrix. If part of a PNG image, the values within the image will be between 0 and 255.\n",
        "from PIL import Image #libreria de imagenes de python\n",
        "from urllib.request import urlopen #Permite leer una direccion electronica"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "h5vw8SWktlHG"
      },
      "source": [
        "First we upload an image from the internet"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "u7yAw_VRtZWK",
        "outputId": "8692f2ff-66c5-46f9-d4eb-a81ab8bd7545",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 287
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "url = 'https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/heroess/images/9/93/Pikachu_SSBU.png/revision/latest?cb=20190511223528&path-prefix=es' \n",
        "filename = urlopen(url)\n",
        "img = Image.open(filename)\n",
        "plt.imshow(img)"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x7fca06cf5748>"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {
            "tags": []
          },
          "execution_count": 9
        },
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "image/png": "\n",
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {
            "tags": [],
            "needs_background": "light"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "juoVg-sNttQV"
      },
      "source": [
        "Let's start with a makeover which means moving all the pixels in the image in one direction, such as horizontally or vertically, while keeping the same image dimensions.\n",
        "\n",
        "The width_shift_range and height_shift_range arguments of the ImageDataGenerator constructor control the amount of horizontal and vertical scrolling respectively.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5FIUITvlPOxo",
        "outputId": "de7466b2-2ac4-4790-d840-8f780f948b4c",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 297
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "# Convertimos la imagen a un arreglo\n",
        "data = img_to_array(img)\n",
        "# realizamos una expansion a una muestra \n",
        "samples = expand_dims(data, 0)\n",
        "# Creamos el aumentador de datos utilizando solo cambio de imgen \n",
        "datagen = ImageDataGenerator(width_shift_range=[-200,200])\n",
        "# preparamos el iterator\n",
        "it = datagen.flow(samples, batch_size=1)\n",
        "# generamos muestras y mostramos los resultados\n",
        "for i in range(9):\n",
        "\tplt.subplot(330 + 1 + i)\n",
        "\t# se generan lotes de imagenes\n",
        "\tbatch = it.next()\n",
        "\timage = batch[0].astype('uint8') #se convierte a un valor valido para poder mostrarlo como imagen \n",
        "\tplt.imshow(image)\n",
        "\tplt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "image/png": "\n",
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 8 Axes>"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {
            "tags": [],
            "needs_background": "light"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EdUDAc7q-tO5"
      },
      "source": [
        ""
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d0zOUUtRtrqg"
      },
      "source": [
        "An image flip means to reverse the rows or columns of pixels in the case of a vertical or horizontal flip, respectively.\n",
        "The magnification is specified by a Boolean argument **horizontal_flip** or **0vertical_flip** for the **ImageDataGenerator** class."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "04-BaA0hUV8w",
        "outputId": "e7dcf1db-9629-457c-fb2b-5402f4215073",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 297
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "datagen = ImageDataGenerator(vertical_flip=True)\n",
        "it = datagen.flow(samples, batch_size=1)\n",
        "for i in range(9):\n",
        "\tplt.subplot(330 + 1 + i)\n",
        "\tbatch = it.next()\n",
        "\timage = batch[0].astype('uint8')\n",
        "\tplt.imshow(image)\n",
        "\tplt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {

            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 8 Axes>"

        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ABaJfwxVyd-T"
      },
      "source": [
        "The amount of zoom is sampled uniformly at random from the zoom region for each dimension (width, height) separately.\n",
        "\n",
        "Floating or [lower limit, upper limit]. Range for random zoom. If it is a float, [lower bound, upper bound] = [1-zoom_range, 1 + zoom_range]"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "lqSWsXf5x3sX",
        "outputId": "04fac067-f63d-4578-ed15-38feb294651e",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 297
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "datagen = ImageDataGenerator(zoom_range=0.5) #float o Rango [lower,upper]\n",
        "it = datagen.flow(samples, batch_size=1)\n",
        "for i in range(9):\n",
        "\tplt.subplot(330 + 1 + i)\n",
        "\tbatch = it.next()\n",
        "\timage = batch[0].astype('uint8')\n",
        "\tplt.imshow(image)\n",
        "\tplt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,

        {
          "output_type": "display_data",

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",

        "id": "XBaQfxWRygEN"
      },
      "source": [
        "The image is randomly rotated clockwise a specified number of degrees from 0 to 360. It is likely to rotate pixels outside of the image frame, leaving areas of the frame with no pixel data, which need to be filled."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",

          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 269
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rotation_range=200)\n",
        "it = datagen.flow(samples, batch_size=1)\n",
        "for i in range(9):\n",
        "\tplt.subplot(330 + 1 + i)\n",
        "\tbatch = it.next()\n",
        "\timage = batch[0].astype('uint8')\n",
        "\tplt.imshow(image)\n",
        "plt.show()"

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ikOuNrk8y2ec"
      },
      "source": [
        "The combination of these techniques allows us to increase the amount of data in the dataset to be used, in many jobs a data augmentation is used to increase the amount of training images and improve the precision of the job."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ayeDLJKhgTEO"
      },
      "source": [
        ""
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6zA-JRpmRlcI"
      },
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "               featurewise_center: Boolean, set the mean of each element to zero of all data.\n",
        "               samplewise_center **: Boolean, set the mean of each sample to zero\n",
        "               featurewise_std_normalization: Boolean, Divide the inputs by the standard deviation (std.) of the data set, based on the characteristics.\n",
        "               samplewise_std_normalization: Boolean, divide each data by its std.\n",
        "               zca_epsilon: The default is 1e-6.\n",
        "               zca_whitening: Boolean, indicates if ZCA whitening is applied."
      ]
    },

        "TextAttack provides us with four methods for data augmentation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rHhLh_K4_h4J"
      },
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "## WordNetAugmenter\n",
        "Augments the text by replacing it with synonyms from the WordNet thesaurus (thesaurus).\n",
        "\n",
        "WordNet is a lexical database for English. Nouns, verbs, adjectives, and adverbs are grouped into sets of cognitive synonyms (synsets), each of which expresses a different concept.\n",
        "WordNet superficially resembles a thesaurus in that it groups words based on their meaning.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QMXCwnbi-5AI",
        "outputId": "2c9e7eaa-bd43-493f-b416-9299b5feffe8",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 55
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "aug = WordNetAugmenter();\n",
        "aug.augment(text)"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "[\"Jhony the multitude are too crazy, don't tell me nothing jesica, let the people enjoy the party \"]"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {
            "tags": []
          },
          "execution_count": 20
        }
      ]
    },

      },
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "## EmbeddingAugmenter\n",

      "source": [
        "\n",
        "## EasyDataAugmenter\n",
        "This augments the text with a combination of Wordnet synonym replacement, word deletion, word order changes, and synonym insertions. All these 4 functionalities occur randomly. So we will get different results every time we run the code. This returns 4 augmented results, unlike the other methods."

        "id": "OMgMmIBr2V31"
      },
      "source": [
        "Googletrans uses the Google Translate Ajax API for language detection and translation.\n",
        "\n",
        "The key parameters for the **translate()** method are:\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **src**: source language. this parameter is optional as **googletrans** will detect it.\n",
        "2. **dest**: target language. Mandatory parameter.\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **text**: the text to be translated from the source language to the target language. Mandatory parameter.\n",

        "\n",
        "\n",
        "When using this method what happens is a retranslation, we go from the original language to a target language and then we return to the original, during this backtranslation, there is a slight change in the sentence between the original text and the backtranslated text, but the general meaning of the sentence is still preserved."
